# BigInt64Array - JavaScript | MDNMDN Web DocsMDN logoMozilla logo

The **`BigInt64Array`** typed array represents an array of 64-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use [`DataView`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/DataView) instead. The contents are initialized to `0n` unless initialization data is explicitly provided. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).

`BigInt64Array` is a subclass of the hidden [`TypedArray`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/TypedArray) class.

## [Try it](#try_it)

## [Constructor](#constructor)

[`BigInt64Array()`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/BigInt64Array/BigInt64Array)

Creates a new `BigInt64Array` object.

